# Sort Into Folders
# AI reads file contents, creates folders by topic, and moves files into the right folders.

[var: SITE = https://microsoft.sharepoint-df.com/teams/ZachDemos/]
[var: LIBRARY = https://microsoft.sharepoint-df.com/teams/ZachDemos/Shared%20Drive%20Dump/]

[section: setup]

Verify the "Shared Drive Dump" library exists with all 8 files flat in the
root — no folders. If folders from a previous run exist, move all files back
to the root and delete the folders.

[navigate: ${LIBRARY}]

[open-chat]

[new-chat]

Confirm 8 files are visible in the root: Q3-revenue-report.xlsx,
brand-guidelines-v2.pdf, onboarding-checklist.docx, server-migration-plan.docx,
holiday-party-invite.png, sales-commission-structure.xlsx, password-policy.pdf,
product-launch-timeline.pptx.

[pause]

[section: demo]

[navigate: ${LIBRARY}]

Every company has that one shared drive where people just dump files. No
folders, no structure, no hope of finding anything. This library has 8 files
from totally different teams all sitting in the root. Let's fix it.

[pause]

[open-chat]

[prompt: Look at all the files in this library. Based on their names and content, suggest a folder structure that would organize them. Group related files together.]

[wait]

Copilot has proposed a folder structure based on reading the actual file
contents — not just guessing from file names. Notice it grouped the revenue
report and commission structure under Finance, and separated IT from HR.
Point out the groupings.

[pause]

Now let's have it actually create the folders and move everything.

[prompt: Create those folders and move each file into the right one.]

[wait]

Refresh the library. Every file has been sorted into a topic folder. It read
the content, figured out the categories, and organized the whole thing. No
drag-and-drop required.

[pause]

[screenshot: tools/screenshots/02-sort-into-folders-final.png]

[section: reset]

Move all files back to the root of the library and delete the folders created
during the demo.

[navigate: ${LIBRARY}]

Move each file from its subfolder back to the root, then delete the empty
folders (Finance, Marketing, HR, IT or whatever Copilot created).

[confirm: Delete all folders created during the demo after moving files back to root]

[new-chat]
